      <item>
        <title>Vega</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Vega is the percentage change of the option’s price relative to an increase of
1% of the volatility.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;\frac{\partial V}{\partial \sigma} = S \sqrt{T}e^{-qT}N&#39;(d1)&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;N&#39;(x) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} e^{-x^2/2}&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(see &lt;a href=&quot;../methods/black-scholes-merton.html&quot;&gt;Black-Scholes-Merton formula&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
